This repository provisions AWS infrastructure for the **Village-development** project using Terraform. It includes VPC, subnets, and EC2 instances with support for multiple AMIs (Ubuntu and Bitnami NGINX).

## Features
- ✅ Fetches the latest Bitnami NGINX AMI from the official AWS account  
- ✅ Fetches the latest Ubuntu AMI from Canonical  
- ✅ Dynamically maps AMI names to IDs via locals  
- ✅ Deploys multiple EC2 instances based on user input  
- ✅ Creates subnets automatically based on VPC CIDR 

---

## Local Variables
```hcl
locals {
  project = "Village-development"
  multi_ami_ids = {
    "nginx"  = data.aws_ami.own_ami_nginx.id
    "ubuntu" = data.aws_ami.own_ami_ubuntu_IND.id
  }
}
```

---

## Variables

### EC2 details
```hcl
variable "ec2_details_input" {
  type = list(object({
    inst_type = string
    AMI_name  = string
  }))
  default = []
}
```

### Subnet count
```hcl
variable "subnet_cnt" {
  type = number
}
```

---

## Data Sources

### VPC
```hcl
data "aws_vpc" "own_vpc" {
  default = true
}
```

### Bitnami NGINX AMI
```hcl
data "aws_ami" "own_ami_nginx" {
  most_recent = true
  owners      = ["679593333241"] # Official Bitnami AWS Account ID

  filter {
    name   = "name"
    values = ["bitnami-nginx-1.31.*-debian-12-amd64-*"]
  }

  filter {
    name   = "virtualization-type"
    values = ["hvm"]
  }
}
```

### Ubuntu AMI
```hcl
data "aws_ami" "own_ami_ubuntu_IND" {
  most_recent = true
  owners      = ["099720109477"] # Canonical's AWS Account ID

  filter {
    name   = "name"
    values = ["ubuntu/images/hvm-ssd/ubuntu-jammy-22.04-amd64-server-*"]
  }

  filter {
    name   = "virtualization-type"
    values = ["hvm"]
  }
}
```

---

## Resources

### Subnets
```hcl
resource "aws_subnet" "multi_own_subnet" {
  count  = var.subnet_cnt
  vpc_id = data.aws_vpc.own_vpc.id
  cidr_block = cidrsubnet(
    data.aws_vpc.own_vpc.cidr_block,
    2,
    count.index + 1
  )

  tags = {
    Name       = "own_subnet_serial_no-${count.index}"
    Grass_root = local.project
  }
}
```

### EC2 Instances
```hcl
resource "aws_instance" "my_ec2" {
  count         = length(var.ec2_details_input)
  instance_type = var.ec2_details_input[count.index].inst_type

  # Dynamic lookup matching user-friendly input string to the resolved AMI map
  ami = local.multi_ami_ids[var.ec2_details_input[count.index].AMI_name]

  subnet_id = aws_subnet.multi_own_subnet[count.index % length(aws_subnet.multi_own_subnet)].id

  tags = {
    Name       = "own_terra-serial-${count.index}"
    Grass_root = local.project
  }
}
```

